{{! Phase E.3 — Visual aid IMAGE generation prompt. }}
{{!
  Variables:
    prompt      str (required, untrusted)
    gradeLevel  str | None
    language    str | None
}}
Create a blackboard chalk-style educational illustration.

Task: Draw a "{{{prompt}}}" for a {{#if gradeLevel}}{{gradeLevel}}{{else}}general{{/if}} classroom.

Style:
- High-fidelity white chalk lines on a dark black background.
- Professional, textbook-quality diagram.

Labels:
- Accurately label the key parts of the diagram.
- Text must be legible, correctly spelled, and spatially correct.
- Use simple block letters.
- **LANGUAGE LOCK (CRITICAL):** All label text MUST be in {{#if language}}{{language}}{{else}}English{{/if}} only. Do NOT mix languages. If the language is Hindi/Tamil/Kannada/Telugu/Marathi/Bengali/Gujarati/Punjabi/Malayalam/Odia, write labels in the native script (e.g. Hindi uses Devanagari: "जड़" not "Jadh" for roots).
